  "text": "Hyperbolic Congruence Singularity (4B): The condition for this singularity occurs when five lines are concurrent with two skew lines. Table 1 shows this singularity configuration. A singular configuration of this type is when 1 transversal 1 3 and 2 is the intersection line between the planes containing 1 and 3 . Arrange 5 so that one of the leg lines (5) intersects both 1 and 2 , 5 is a generic point on it, and the other leg line (6) does not have a constraint. The corresponding leg lines are linearly independent, thus forming a hyperbolic congruence. In this condition, four planes meet, [CITATION_1] and the platform intersects 2 , which is the intersection of 1 and 3 , at the point that link 5 meets 2 . In the same way, the three eqml:",
